				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-11705",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in Mozilla. The Mozilla Foundation's Security Advisory describes the following issue: `NSC_DeriveKey` inadvertently assumed that the `phKey` parameter is always non-NULL. When it was passed as NULL, a segmentation fault (SEGV) occurred, leading to crashes. This behavior conflicted with the PKCS#11 v3.0 specification, which allows `phKey` to be NULL for certain mechanisms. \n            STATEMENT: Red Hat Product Security rates the severity of this flaw as determined by the Mozilla Foundation Security Advisory.",
